    "rich_text_ppGgwa": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "name": "Rich text",
      "settings": {
        "rt_subtitle": "BLUE, FOR A GREENER FUTURE",
        "rt_title": "THE GRAND SOLEIL BLUE",
        "rt_text1": "Grand Soleil BLUE is the new 33-foot daysailer by Cantiere del Pardo — a yacht designed to simplify sailing and offer a stylish, enjoyable experience on the water.\n Elegant, fast, and incredibly easy to handle even solo, BLUE is perfect for day trips or weekend escapes. A modern weekender that brings sailing back to its purest form: freedom, simplicity, and a direct connection with the water.\n\n\nBorn from the collaboration between Matteo Polli (naval architecture), Nauta Design (interior and exterior design) Grand Soleil BLUE is built using rComposite®️ technology, patented by the Italian startup nlcomp (pioneers in sustainable materials), moreover is also the first 100% recyclable production sailboat made in Italy. A project where refined design meets environmental responsibility through advanced technologies and low-impact solutions.\n\n\nEvery design choice reflects a clear vision: to create a beautiful, lightweight, and immediate yacht — ready to enjoy in your free time, with no waiting, no constraints.\nAn invitation to rediscover the true pleasure of sailing, at your own pace.\n\n\nFor those who prefer, it will also be available with a traditional laminated hull and an internal combustion engine.",
        "rt-cta_label": "",
        "rt-cta_link": "",
        "enable_alt_style": false,
        "alignment_mobile": "left",
        "alignment_desktop": "center",
        "pt_mobile": 40,
